ENTRY            F0694   20251224   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0694001   20251224   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 13         29
TITLE      Energy-dependent coherence width of 28Si at excitation
           energies between 22 and 33 MeV
AUTHOR     (J.D.A.Roeders,L.W.Put,A.G.Drentje,A.Van Der Woude)
INSTITUTE  (2NEDRUG,1USAORL)
REFERENCE  (J,NCL,2,209,1969)
REL-REF    (I,,L.W.Put,J,NP/A,112,561,1968) Experimental
           arrangement was described.
           (O,F0646001,A.G.Drentje+,J,PL/B,32,356,1970)
             - Partial differential cross sections presented.
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2NEDRUG) Philips prototype 30 MeV AVF-cyclotron.
SAMPLE     Target of MG-24 was used.
INC-SPECT  Energy of alpha particles is in the range from 18 MeV
           to 27 MeV.
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Detectors were placed at eight angles between
           80 degrees and 164 degrees (lab.)
ANALYSIS   Excitation functions were obtained in steps of
           35, 40 and 100 keV. Statistical analysis was applied to
           56 measured excitation functions.
CORRECTION The values of resonance width Gamma(n) were corrected
           for energy resolution and finite range of data effects.
           Half-widths of Gamma(g) needed extra correction for
            "damping" of excitation functions. Values of resonance
           width Gamma(p) were corrected for energy resolution,
           step size and counting statistics.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) Uncertainty in resonance width. No source
           of uncertainty is given.
HISTORY    (20040810C)
           (20110808U) SD: space from author's name deleted.
           (20251224A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              29
COMMON               1          3
EN-RSL
KEV
 30.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           36
SUBENT        F0694002   20251224   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  4         10
REACTION  1(12-MG-24(A,0),,EN)
          2(12-MG-24(A,INL),,WID)
COMMENT    DATA2 is a mean value of an averaged value of width
           from normal autocorrelation functions, an averaged
           value of width from autocorrelation functions of
           trend-reduced excitation functions and an averaged
           value from a number of maxima in the excitation
           functions.
STATUS     (TABLE,,J.D.A.Roeders+,J,NCL,2,209,1969) Table 1
HISTORY    (20251224U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB              10
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 4          4
DATA-MIN  1DATA-MAX  1DATA      2DATA-ERR  2
MEV        MEV        KEV        KEV
       17.7       20.4        81.        14.
       19.0       23.7        96.        15.
       22.9       25.2        97.        17.
       23.0       27.0       116.        29.
ENDDATA              6
ENDSUBENT           21
